{"lemma":"نَهار","slug":"نَهار","root":"ن.ه.ر","root_slug":"ن-ه-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ه-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"نَهار","root":"نهر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":57},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40636"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%B1"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"daytime, day","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chick of a bustard (حُبَارَى (ḥubārā)), curlew (كَرَوَان (karawān)), sandgrouse (قَطًا (qaṭan)) and/or owl (بُوم (būm))","tags":["countable","obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cock of a bustard or owl","tags":["countable","obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"possibly related to Aramaic נְהַר."},"ipa":["/na.haːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40636","headword_ar":"نَهَارٌ","root":"nhr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Day;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"day-time; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolN","text_ar":"لَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broad daylight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from sunrise to sunset:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K:) this is the original signification: (TA;) or this is the signification in the vulgar conventional language: but in the classical language it signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time from the rising of the dawn to sunset:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light between the rising of the dawn and sunset:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and so accord. to the lawyers: (TA:) in the trads., it is the whiteness of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nhAr","text_ar":"نهار"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the blackness of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lyl","text_ar":"ليل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and there is nothing intervening between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lyl","text_ar":"ليل"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nhAr","text_ar":"نهار"},{"kind":"text","text":": but sometimes the Arabs amplified, and applied"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nhAr","text_ar":"نهار"},{"kind":"text","text":"to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time from the clear shining of the dawn to the setting"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sun"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb.) or (so accord. to the TA. but in some copies of the K, and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spreading of the light"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is a cause"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sight"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its dispersion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) in this explanation in the L, in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@fotiraAquhu","text_ar":"وَا@فْتِرَاقُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@jotimaAEuhu","text_ar":"وَا@جْتِمَاعُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its collecting together"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) it is also syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomN","text_ar":"يَوْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and is so when used without restriction in the non-fundamental sciences of religion, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfuruwE","text_ar":"الفُرُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":",) as in the phrases"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sumo nahaArFA","text_ar":"صُمْ نَهَارًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fast thou a day"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iEomalo nahaArFA","text_ar":"اـِعْمَلْ نَهَارًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"work thou a day"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and it may be so used, or in its proper classical sense, when prefixed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawom","text_ar":"يَوْم"},{"kind":"text","text":", governing the latter in the gen. case: (Msb:) it has no proper dual, (Mgh, Msb,) and no proper pl., (S, Mgh, Msb, K, (like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*aAbN","text_ar":"عَذَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAbN","text_ar":"سَرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) the former of which, however, has a pl. assigned to it [by Zj and] in the K, namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEo*ibapN","text_ar":"اَعْذِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MF;) [and respecting the latter see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araAbN","text_ar":"شَرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$","text_ar":"ش"},{"kind":"text","text":";] [for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nhAr","text_ar":"نهار"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a name applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawom","text_ar":"يَوْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"day"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolN","text_ar":"لَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to every"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolap","text_ar":"لَيْلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or night]: one does not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahaArN wanahaAraAni","text_ar":"نَهَارٌ وَنَهَارَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolN walayolaAni","text_ar":"لَيْلٌ وَلَيْلَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but the sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nhAr","text_ar":"نهار"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomN","text_ar":"يَوْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) and the dual,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomaAni","text_ar":"يَوْمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA:) and the pl.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ay~aAmN","text_ar":"اَيَّامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb:) and the contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ywomN","text_ar":"يوْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapN","text_ar":"لَيْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", so says Az, on the authority of AHeyth (TA:) or it has pls.: namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anohurN","text_ar":"اَنْهُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, S, K,) a pl. of pauc., (S,) in some lexicons"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anohirapN","text_ar":"اَنْهِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) also a pl. of pauc.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuhurN","text_ar":"نُهُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) a pl. of mult. (S) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naharN","text_ar":"نَهَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Ibn-Keysán cites the following ex.,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"lawolaA Alv~ariydaAn lamutonaA biAlD~umuro\n                      \n                     \n                        variydu layolK wavriydN biAln~ahuro"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Were it not for the two thereeds"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"messes of crumbled bread moistened with broth"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"we had died of leanness: the thereed of night, and thereed in the day-times"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","Mgh","Msb","K","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}